Description: Gold-plated bronze bracelet, now broken into two sections, composed of a tube tapering to wires at each end, twisted around each other.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: John de Monins Johnson
Curator's comments: Cf., V&A M. 15-1966 and M. 15-1969, records for which can be accessed at http://collections.vam.ac.uk/, (last accessed August 2012); Stolz 2007, nos 85–90; Marshall 1969, nos 2807, 2808. Marshall, F. H. 1969. Catalogue of the jewellery: Greek, Etruscan, and Roman in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum. London: The Trustees of the British Museum. Stolz, Y. 2007. Byzantine jewellery and related small finds from the underwater excavations in the Bay of Abuqir in Egypt: Their typology, production and context. Unpublished PhD diss. Oxford University.
